# 🔥 CipherGrid — Hard Challenge Tasks

After a deep analysis of every source file in the project, here are **10 challenging tasks** ranked by difficulty. Each involves meaningful code changes across both the server and client.

---

## Task 1: Turn Timer with Auto-Pass ⏱️
**Difficulty:** ★★★★☆ | **Files:** 6+ | **Full-stack**

Add a configurable turn timer (e.g. 90 seconds for spymaster, 60 seconds for operative guessing). When the timer expires, the turn auto-passes to the other team.

**What to change:**
- **Server** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add `turnTimer`, `turnStartedAt` to [GameState](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/types.ts#33-50) and [ClientGameState](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/types.ts#66-80)
- **Server** — [engine.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts): start timer on turn switch, handle expiry via `setInterval` or per-action checks
- **Server** — [handler.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/ws/handler.ts): broadcast `TIMER_TICK` or `TIMER_EXPIRED` events; auto-call [switchTurn()](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts#285-300) on expiry
- **Client** — New `Timer.tsx` component: circular countdown animation with Framer Motion
- **Client** — [TeamBar.tsx](file:///d:/codenames/client/components/TeamBar.tsx) / game page: integrate the timer display
- **Client** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add timer-related fields to state types

**Why it's hard:** Requires server-side interval management per room, syncing timer state across clients, handling edge cases (timer expire during flip, disconnect/reconnect with timer), and cleaning up intervals on room deletion.

---

## Task 2: "Play Again" — Server-Side Rematch System 🔄
**Difficulty:** ★★★★☆ | **Files:** 5+ | **Full-stack**

Currently "Play Again" just redirects to lobby (`/`). Implement a real rematch system where players can vote to replay in the same room with a fresh board, swapping team sides.

**What to change:**
- **Server** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add `VOTE_REMATCH` client event, `REMATCH_VOTES` server event
- **Server** — [engine.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts): new `resetGame()` function that clears the board, swaps starting team, resets phase to `lobby`
- **Server** — [handler.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/ws/handler.ts): `handleVoteRematch()` — track votes, when all vote yes → `resetGame()` and broadcast
- **Client** — [GameOver.tsx](file:///d:/codenames/client/components/GameOver.tsx): replace redirect with "Vote Rematch" button showing vote count (e.g., "3/4 voted")
- **Client** — game page: handle `REMATCH_VOTES` event to update UI

**Why it's hard:** Requires vote tracking per player, handling disconnected voters, resetting game state without destroying the room/socket connections, and keeping players connected through the transition.

---

## Task 3: In-Game Team Chat 💬
**Difficulty:** ★★★★☆ | **Files:** 6+ | **Full-stack**

Add a real-time team-only chat alongside the Action Log. Spymasters of the same team should NOT share a chat channel (to prevent cheating). Operatives can chat within their team.

**What to change:**
- **Server** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add `CHAT_MESSAGE` client event, `CHAT_BROADCAST` server event, `ChatMessage` interface
- **Server** — [handler.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/ws/handler.ts): `handleChatMessage()` — validate sender, only broadcast to teammates (excluding other team's spymaster from seeing)
- **Server** — [engine.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts) or new `chat.ts` module: chat history storage per room
- **Client** — New `TeamChat.tsx` component with message input, scroll-to-bottom, team-colored messages
- **Client** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add chat types
- **Client** — game page: integrate chat alongside or tabbed with ActionLog

**Why it's hard:** Information security is critical—must ensure spymasters can't leak information. Need to handle the chat vs role permissions matrix carefully, persist chat history within the game session, and handle reconnection (should see previous messages).

---

## Task 4: Custom Word Packs 📦
**Difficulty:** ★★★☆☆ | **Files:** 5+ | **Full-stack**

Let the room creator select from multiple word packs (Classic, Movies, Science, Food, etc.) or create a custom word pack before the game starts.

**What to change:**
- **Server** — [data/words.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/data/words.ts): restructure into a `Map<string, string[]>` of named word packs
- **Server** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add `wordPack` field to [GameState](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/types.ts#33-50), `SET_WORD_PACK` client event
- **Server** — [engine.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts): [generateBoard()](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts#18-43) accepts word pack parameter, validate pack has ≥25 words
- **Server** — [handler.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/ws/handler.ts): `handleSetWordPack()` — only room creator can set, only during lobby
- **Client** — Lobby game page: word pack selector dropdown/cards with preview
- **Client** — New `WordPackSelector.tsx` component

**Why it's hard:** Needs "room creator" permissions concept (currently no admin/host concept exists), validation that custom packs have enough unique words, and clean UX for pack selection.

---

## Task 5: Spectator Mode 👀
**Difficulty:** ★★★★★ | **Files:** 6+ | **Full-stack**

Allow players to join as spectators who can watch the game without being on a team. Spectators see the operative view (hidden cards) and cannot interact with the game board.

**What to change:**
- **Server** — [types.ts](file:///d:/codenames/client/lib/types.ts): add `'spectator'` to roles, update [PlayerRole](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/types.ts#7-8) union
- **Server** — [engine.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts): [getFilteredState()](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts#331-374) must filter spectators correctly (operative-like view), [startGame()](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts#80-115) should ignore spectators for team validation, [checkAllReady()](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts#322-330) should skip spectators
- **Server** — [handler.ts](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/ws/handler.ts): allow joining without team selection, handle spectator-specific logic
- **Client** — Lobby: add "Watch as Spectator" option alongside team/role selection
- **Client** — Game page: show spectator badge, disable all interactions, show spectator count
- **Client** — [TeamBar.tsx](file:///d:/codenames/client/components/TeamBar.tsx): display spectator list separately

**Why it's hard:** Touches nearly every validation path. Must ensure spectators can't accidentally be counted for ready checks, team balance, or game start requirements. [getFilteredState](file:///d:/codenames/server/src/game/engine.ts#331-374) must be carefully extended. Spectators should gracefully transition if they want to join mid-game (or be blocked).

